# Secrets & Certificates
*.pem
*.crt
*.csr
*.p12
*.pfx
*.jks
*.keystore
*.p8
secrets/
# Exception: a product's SOPS/age-ENCRYPTED secrets are committed (they are safe
# at rest and must survive a fresh checkout); the age private key / plaintext never are.
!packages/products/*/secrets/
packages/products/*/secrets/*.key
packages/products/*/secrets/*.age
packages/products/*/secrets/*.plain
# Exception: a product's SOPS/age-ENCRYPTED config-backup snapshots are committed
# (safe at rest, and the only way a fresh checkout restores each container's
# essential config). Only the `.enc` ciphertext is tracked; any decrypted plaintext
# scratch (`*.plain`) is re-ignored as defense-in-depth so a stray decrypt can never
# be staged. Mirrors the `secrets/` block above.
!packages/products/*/config-backup/
packages/products/*/config-backup/*.plain
packages/products/*/config-backup/**/*.plain
.secrets/
.secrets
credentials.json
service-account*.json
*-credentials.json
.cloudflared/

# Environment Variables
.env
.env.*
.dev.vars
.dev.vars.*

# Logs
logs/
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
lerna-debug.log*
# Exception: hand-authored .log fixtures for parity tests (emit-trp-failure
# reads a real log file, so the fixture MUST be a .log to exercise the code
# path). The exception narrows to the parity-test fixtures dir only.
!packages/products/trp/tests/fixtures/**/*.log

